          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Argon bombardments: Reaction product Cl-38(37 min)",
                "   contained Cl-39(55.5min) impurity and decay curve",
                "   analysis was made to discriminate Cl-38 activity.",
                "Zinc bombardments: Reaction product consisted of Cu-61",
                "   (3.32hr), Cu-64(12.8hr) and Cu-67(61.5hr). Decay",
                "   curves were analyzed by least-squares method."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Absolute errors were estimated from a consideration of",
                "all factors affecting the measurement, but this",
                "estimate is inevitably somewhat subjective.",
                "Uncertainty in deuteron beam energy is about 0.1 MeV",
                "at 15 MeV and about 0.15-0.2 MeV at 10 MeV. This",
                "uncertainty increases rapidly with decreasing energy",
                "below 5 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Bombarding natural zinc, three reactions Zn-66(d,a),",
                "Zn-67(d,n+a) and Zn-64(d,2p) are possible to produce",
                "Cu-64. In order to determine each component in the",
                "summed excitation function, Zn-68 enriched zinc",
                "targets (of different Zn-64:Zn-66:Zn-67 abundance",
                "ratios) was also bombarded. If reasonable estimates of",
                "cross sections for Zn-66(d,a) are obtained, cross",
                "sections for other two reactions can be deduced solving",
                "the simultaneous equations. Considering the Q-values",
                "and Coulomb barriers, data for Zn-0(d,X) reaction at",
                "deuteron energies below about 8 MeV is probably from",
                "only Zn-66(d,a)Cu-64 reaction. The shape of excitation",
                "function of Zn-66(d,a) at higher energies was assumed",
                "from (d,a) reactions on nuclei around this mass region",
                "experimental data for Zn-64(d,a+n)Cu-61 were also used",
                "to estimate the Zn-67(d,a+n) excitation curve."
              ]
            }
          ],
